          "&lt;p&gt;Given:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Seven people A, B, C, D, E, F and G are sitting in a straight line facing the north.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;G and C are sitting at the ends of the line not necessarily in the same order.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;F is sitting to the immediate right of G and the immediate left of D.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;E is sitting to the immediate right of D. A is sitting second to the right of E. B is sitting second to the left of C.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/qImage681b5cea8a310b03a1676930.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Thus, A is sitting between B and C.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 4&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n",
