          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Himachal Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;As per Census 2011, Himachal Pradesh recorded the &lt;strong&gt;highest literacy rate among northern states&lt;/strong&gt; with a literacy rate of 82.80%.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Himachal Pradesh&amp;#39;s focus on education policies and rural literacy programs played a key role in achieving this milestone.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The literacy rate for males in Himachal Pradesh stood at 89.53%, while for females it was 75.93%, showcasing efforts toward &lt;strong&gt;gender inclusivity in education&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The state invested heavily in primary education and teacher training programs to improve its literacy rate.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Himachal Pradesh ranks &lt;strong&gt;11th overall in literacy rates&lt;/strong&gt; across India as per Census 2011 data.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Literacy Rate Definition:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Literacy rate refers to the percentage of people aged 7 and above who can read and write with understanding.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Census 2011 classified literacy into male and female literacy rates to assess gender disparity in education.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Focus Areas in Himachal Pradesh:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Emphasis on universal primary education and mid-day meal schemes to boost enrolment.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Implementation of adult literacy programs to bridge gaps in literacy among older age groups.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Strengthening of infrastructure like schools and libraries in rural areas.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comparison with Other Northern States:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Punjab (76.68%) and Uttarakhand (78.82%) follow Himachal Pradesh but lag behind in overall literacy rate.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Haryana&amp;rsquo;s literacy rate stood at 75.55%, significantly lower compared to Himachal Pradesh.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Literacy Rate (Census 2011):&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The overall literacy rate of India was 74.04% in 2011, with Kerala leading at 93.91%.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Himachal Pradesh&amp;rsquo;s literacy rate was above the national average, showcasing its focus on educational reforms.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
