          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PM Rashtriya Krishi Vikas Yojana&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;PM Rashtriya Krishi Vikas Yojana (RKVY)&lt;/strong&gt; aims to achieve food security, sustainable agriculture, and self-sufficiency by promoting growth in the agricultural sector.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;It is a state plan scheme launched in 2007 but restructured as &lt;strong&gt;RKVY-Remunerative Approaches for Agriculture and Allied sector Rejuvenation (RKVY-RAFTAAR)&lt;/strong&gt; in 2017 to focus on pre- and post-harvest infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Under this scheme, funds are provided to states as grants for agricultural development, ensuring decentralization and flexibility for local needs.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The scheme also supports innovation and technology adoption in agriculture to increase productivity and profitability for farmers.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;It aligns with the government&amp;#39;s goal of doubling farmers&amp;#39; incomes by 2024, with a focus on value addition, market linkages, and sustainable farming practices.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sustainable Agriculture&lt;/strong&gt;\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It involves practices that maintain soil health, conserve water, and reduce dependency on chemical inputs.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Techniques include crop rotation, organic farming, integrated pest management, and agroforestry.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Sustainable agriculture ensures long-term productivity while minimizing environmental harm.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Food Security Mission (NFSM)&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Launched in 2007-08, it aims to increase the production of rice, wheat, pulses, and coarse cereals to meet the growing demand.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It focuses on area expansion, productivity enhancement, and restoring soil fertility.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The mission operates through cluster demonstrations, distribution of quality seeds, and resource conservation technologies.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Mission on Oilseeds and Oil Palm (NMOOP)&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It was launched in 2014-15 to augment the production of edible oils by promoting oilseeds and oil palm cultivation.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The mission aims to achieve self-sufficiency in edible oil production and reduce dependency on imports.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It emphasizes increasing the area under cultivation, improving productivity, and adopting high-yielding varieties.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Krishi Infrastructure Fund&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Launched in 2020, it provides financial support for building post-harvest infrastructure and community farming assets.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The fund has a corpus of Rs. 1 lakh crore, focusing on storage, processing, and value-addition facilities.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It empowers farmers and Farmer Producer Organizations (FPOs) to gain better market access and reduce wastage.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
