          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;November&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Rann Utsav&lt;/strong&gt; is an annual cultural festival celebrated in the Rann of Kutch, Gujarat.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;It begins in the month of &lt;strong&gt;November&lt;/strong&gt; and continues until February, showcasing the vibrant culture, crafts, and traditions of Gujarat.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The festival is organized by the Gujarat Tourism Department and attracts tourists from across the globe.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Key attractions include the &lt;strong&gt;white salt desert&lt;/strong&gt;, folk music and dance performances, camel rides, adventure sports, and traditional Gujarati cuisine.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The event is held in Dhordo village, often referred to as the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Tent City&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; due to its luxurious tent accommodations.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rann of Kutch&lt;/strong&gt;\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The Rann of Kutch is a seasonal salt marsh located in the Thar Desert in Gujarat.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It spans an area of approximately 7,500 square kilometers, making it one of the largest salt deserts in the world.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The region is known for its unique geography, biodiversity, and cultural significance.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance of Rann Utsav&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The festival highlights the art, craft, and cultural heritage of Gujarat.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It boosts tourism and contributes significantly to the local economy.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It provides a platform for artisans and performers to showcase their talent and promote indigenous crafts.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activities at Rann Utsav&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Adventure activities such as paramotoring, ATV rides, and hot air ballooning are popular among visitors.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Shopping for handmade crafts, jewelry, and textiles is a key attraction.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Visitors can enjoy stargazing, as the desert offers clear night skies.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Best Time to Visit&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The ideal time to attend Rann Utsav is between November and February when the weather is pleasant.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The full moon nights during the festival offer breathtaking views of the white desert illuminated by moonlight.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
