        value:
          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;One-and-a-half times the cost of production&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;In the Union Budget for 2018-19, the government announced that the Minimum Support Price (MSP) for all principal crops would be set at &lt;strong&gt;one-and-a-half times (1.5x) the cost of production&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;This decision aimed to ensure remunerative prices for farmers and address the issue of agrarian distress in the country.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The MSP calculation is based on the comprehensive cost of production, including expenses such as seeds, fertilizers, labor, irrigation, and other inputs.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The announcement was in line with the Swaminathan Commission&amp;#39;s recommendations, which advocated fixing MSP at least 50% higher than the cost of production.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The initiative was primarily targeted at improving farmers&amp;#39; income and boosting agricultural productivity in India.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Support Price (MSP):&lt;/strong&gt;\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;MSP is a form of market intervention by the Government of India to safeguard farmers against sharp price falls during bumper production years.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The MSP is announced for 22 mandated crops and is determined by the Cabinet Committee on Economic Affairs (CCEA).&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It is based on the recommendations of the Commission for Agricultural Costs and Prices (CACP).&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Swaminathan Commission:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The National Commission on Farmers, chaired by Dr. M.S. Swaminathan, recommended fixing MSP at least 50% above the cost of production (C2).&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The formula includes both input costs (A2) and the imputed value of family labor (FL).&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Types of Costs in MSP Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A2:&lt;/strong&gt; Includes out-of-pocket expenses like seeds, fertilizers, and labor.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A2+FL:&lt;/strong&gt; A2 costs plus the imputed value of unpaid family labor.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C2:&lt;/strong&gt; Comprehensive cost, including A2+FL and the rental value of owned land and interest on fixed capital.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Implementation and Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The 1.5x MSP policy ensures better income for farmers and reduces their dependence on informal credit systems.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It also incentivizes crop diversification and adoption of sustainable farming practices.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
