        value:
          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use of modern irrigation techniques&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The Green Revolution introduced advanced agricultural practices, including the use of &lt;strong&gt;modern irrigation techniques&lt;/strong&gt; like drip and sprinkler systems for water conservation.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Modern irrigation methods ensured &lt;strong&gt;efficient utilization of water resources&lt;/strong&gt; and helped increase crop yields, especially in areas with scarce water supply.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;These techniques supported the cultivation of high-yield variety (HYV) crops, which required &lt;strong&gt;timely and adequate water supply&lt;/strong&gt; for optimal growth.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The adoption of modern irrigation systems reduced dependency on &lt;strong&gt;monsoon rainfall&lt;/strong&gt;, making agriculture more resilient to climate variability.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Modern irrigation played a critical role in transforming India&amp;rsquo;s agricultural sector during the Green Revolution, contributing to &lt;strong&gt;food security and self-sufficiency&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High-Yield Variety (HYV) Seeds:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;HYV seeds were developed to produce higher output per hectare compared to traditional seeds.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;These seeds often required proper irrigation, fertilizers, and pesticides for maximum productivity.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chemical Fertilizers and Pesticides:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The Green Revolution encouraged the use of chemical fertilizers to enhance soil fertility and crop production.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Pesticides were introduced to protect crops from pests and diseases, ensuring a more stable yield.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanization of Agriculture:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Tractors, harvesters, and other machinery replaced traditional animal labor, significantly improving efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Mechanization allowed large-scale farming and reduced manual labor dependency.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact on Food Security:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The Green Revolution helped India achieve self-sufficiency in food grains, reducing dependency on imports.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It significantly contributed to reducing hunger and malnutrition in the country.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Environmental Concerns:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Excessive use of fertilizers and pesticides caused soil degradation and water pollution.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Modern irrigation techniques, though efficient, sometimes led to waterlogging and salinization in certain areas.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
