          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jharkhand&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Droupadi Murmu&lt;/strong&gt; served as the &lt;strong&gt;9th Governor of Jharkhand&lt;/strong&gt; from May 18, 2015, to July 12, 2021.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;She was the &lt;strong&gt;first tribal woman&lt;/strong&gt; to be appointed as the Governor of Jharkhand since the state&amp;#39;s formation in 2000.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;During her tenure, she was known for her work in &lt;strong&gt;tribal welfare&lt;/strong&gt; and governance in the state.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Her appointment as the Governor was widely seen as a recognition of her contributions to public service and her commitment to social causes.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;She has now become the &lt;strong&gt;15th President of India&lt;/strong&gt;, making history as the first tribal woman to hold this prestigious position.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governorship in India:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The Governor is the &lt;strong&gt;constitutional head of a state&lt;/strong&gt;, appointed by the President of India for a term of five years.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The Governor acts as the &lt;strong&gt;representative of the central government&lt;/strong&gt; in the state.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Key responsibilities include giving assent to bills, summoning or dissolving the state legislature, and overseeing the functioning of the state government.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jharkhand:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Jharkhand is a state in eastern India, carved out of Bihar in &lt;strong&gt;2000&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;It is rich in natural resources and is known for its tribal culture and traditions.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The state has a significant tribal population, comprising around &lt;strong&gt;26% of its total population&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Droupadi Murmu&amp;rsquo;s Background:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;She hails from the &lt;strong&gt;Santhal tribal community&lt;/strong&gt; in Odisha.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;She began her political career as a member of the &lt;strong&gt;Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP)&lt;/strong&gt; and served in various capacities in Odisha, including as a minister.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;Her rise to becoming the President of India is a &lt;strong&gt;landmark achievement&lt;/strong&gt; for tribal representation in Indian politics.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role as President of India:&lt;/strong&gt;\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The President is the &lt;strong&gt;head of state&lt;/strong&gt; and the supreme commander of the armed forces in India.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;The President&amp;#39;s role is largely ceremonial, but they have significant powers in times of political crises, such as the dissolution of Lok Sabha or the imposition of President&amp;#39;s Rule in a state.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;As President, Droupadi Murmu has emphasized &lt;strong&gt;inclusive development&lt;/strong&gt; and the empowerment of marginalized communities.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
