        value:
          "&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Total amount Mahesh has = ₹1617&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Rate of interest = 10% compounded annually&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Vijay&amp;#39;s investment period = 15 years&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Ajay&amp;#39;s investment period = 16 years&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Vijay and Ajay received the same amount after their respective investment periods.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Compound Interest Formula: A = P(1 + r/100)&lt;sup&gt;t&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Where:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;A = Final amount&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;P = Principal amount&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;r = Rate of interest&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;t = Time (in years)&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Let Mahesh give Vijay ₹x and Ajay ₹(1617 - x).&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;According to the question, the final amounts for Vijay and Ajay are equal:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;x(1 + 10/100)&lt;sup&gt;15&lt;/sup&gt; = (1617 - x)(1 + 10/100)&lt;sup&gt;16&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x(1.1)&lt;sup&gt;15&lt;/sup&gt; = (1617 - x)(1.1)&lt;sup&gt;16&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = (1617 - x)(1.1)&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 1617 &amp;times; 1.1 - x &amp;times; 1.1&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x + 1.1x = 1617 &amp;times; 1.1&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 2.1x = 1778.7&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 1778.7 / 2.1&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 847&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mahesh gave Vijay ₹847.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n",
