          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 4&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;scratching their heads&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to be puzzled or confused about something. (असमंजस में होना)\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The students were &lt;strong&gt;scratching their heads&lt;/strong&gt; trying to solve the tricky math problem.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, &amp;quot;Her explanation was so convoluted that it left everyone confused,&amp;quot; the idiom &amp;quot;scratching their heads&amp;quot; perfectly fits as it describes people being perplexed due to the explanation. (असमंजस के कारण)&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Biting the bullet&lt;/strong&gt; (गंभीर स्थिति को सहन करना): To face a difficult or unpleasant situation with courage.\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She decided to &lt;strong&gt;bite the bullet&lt;/strong&gt; and confront her boss about the unfair treatment.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turning a blind eye&lt;/strong&gt; (जानबूझकर अनदेखा करना): To ignore something intentionally.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The manager &lt;strong&gt;turned a blind eye&lt;/strong&gt; to the employee&amp;rsquo;s minor mistakes to maintain harmony in the team.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stealing the show&lt;/strong&gt; (सबका ध्यान आकर्षित करना): To attract the most attention or admiration in a performance or event.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The young dancer &lt;strong&gt;stole the show&lt;/strong&gt; with her breathtaking performance.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
