        value:
          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 4&lt;/b&gt; i.e.,&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;play his cards right&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Play his cards right&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to using one&amp;#39;s resources or strategies wisely to achieve the best possible outcome. (समस्याओं से निपटने के लिए समझदारी से काम करना)\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; If he &lt;strong&gt;plays his cards right&lt;/strong&gt;, he could become the next CEO of the company.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the most appropriate idiom for maximizing advantages in negotiations is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;play his cards right&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;play his cards right&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Play it safe&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;सावधानी से खेलना&lt;/span&gt;): Acting cautiously and avoiding risks.\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She always prefers to &lt;strong&gt;play it safe&lt;/strong&gt; when trying new things.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Play it by ear&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अनुमान के आधार पर कार्य करना&lt;/span&gt;): To act spontaneously and according to the situation without a fixed plan.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Let&amp;#39;s not plan everything in detail now, we&amp;#39;ll just &lt;strong&gt;play it by ear&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Play it by air&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;हवा में खेलना&lt;/span&gt;): This phrase is typically a mistaken version of &amp;quot;play it by ear&amp;quot; and does not have a recognized idiomatic meaning.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Incorrect usage: He decided to &lt;strong&gt;play it by air&lt;/strong&gt; and see what happens during the trip. Correct usage: He decided to play it by ear and see what happens during the trip.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
