          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Primitive&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;rudimentary&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that is basic, elementary, or in its earliest stages of development. (मौलिक / प्रारंभिक)\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She has only a &lt;strong&gt;rudimentary &lt;/strong&gt;understanding of mathematics, so she finds advanced calculations challenging.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Primitive&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means something that is simple or undeveloped, often referring to an early stage of development or basic form. (आदिम / सरल)\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The tools used in the Stone Age were &lt;strong&gt;primitive &lt;/strong&gt;compared to modern machinery.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Hence, the synonym of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;rudimentary&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;primitive&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Primitive&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exquisite&lt;/strong&gt; (अत्यंत सुंदर): Extremely beautiful and delicate.\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The artist&amp;#39;s work is known for its &lt;strong&gt;exquisite &lt;/strong&gt;detail and craftsmanship.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mysterious&lt;/strong&gt; (रहस्यमय): Something that is difficult or impossible to understand or explain.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The sudden disappearance of the ship in the Bermuda Triangle remains &lt;strong&gt;mysterious&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creative&lt;/strong&gt; (रचनात्मक): Involving the use of imagination or original ideas to create something new.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The designer&amp;#39;s &lt;strong&gt;creative &lt;/strong&gt;approach helped bring innovation to the project.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
