          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 4 (Trick)&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Dodge&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to avoid something by a quick movement or clever manoeuvre. (बचाना)\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;He &lt;strong&gt;dodged &lt;/strong&gt;the ball thrown at him by quickly stepping aside.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Trick&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a clever or deceitful action meant to achieve a goal or outwit someone. (चालाकी/चाल)\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The magician performed an amazing &lt;strong&gt;trick &lt;/strong&gt;that left the audience stunned.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Hence, &amp;quot;Dodge&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Trick&amp;quot; are synonymous as they both involve clever or skilful actions to avoid or deceive.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 4 (Trick)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Panic&lt;/strong&gt; (घबराहट): A sudden overwhelming fear or anxiety that may cause irrational behaviour.\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She felt &lt;strong&gt;panic &lt;/strong&gt;when she realized she had lost her wallet.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opine&lt;/strong&gt; (मत व्यक्त करना): To express an opinion about something.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He &lt;strong&gt;opined &lt;/strong&gt;that the new policy would benefit small businesses.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Display&lt;/strong&gt; (प्रदर्शन): To show or exhibit something publicly.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The artist&amp;#39;s paintings were &lt;strong&gt;displayed &lt;/strong&gt;at the gallery last weekend.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
