          "&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;stepping&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;stepping&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means to lift and set down one&amp;#39;s foot or one foot after the other. (चरण करना)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The phrase &amp;quot;stepping onto the stage&amp;quot; is a common expression used when someone is about to start a performance or speech.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The other options: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;stuck&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;hit&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;made&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; do not fit the context appropriately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complete Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Santra took a deep breath before &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;stepping&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; onto the stage to deliver her speech.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stuck (फंसना)&lt;/strong&gt;: means to be caught or fixed in a particular position.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hit (मारना)&lt;/strong&gt;: means to come into contact with forcefully.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Made (बनाया)&lt;/strong&gt;: means created or formed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
