          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 1 (Back against the wall)&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Back against the wall&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to being in a very difficult situation with few or no options available to escape or resolve it. (मुश्किल स्थिति में फंस जाना)\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;With mounting debts and no job, he felt like his &lt;strong&gt;back was against the wall&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Difficult circumstance with no escape at all&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; matches the meaning of the idiom &amp;quot;Back against the wall,&amp;quot; indicating helplessness in a tough situation. (मुसीबत में फंसा हुआ)\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The agents were stuck in a dangerous mission with no way out, making them feel like their &lt;strong&gt;backs were against the wall&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Hence, the idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Back against the wall&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the most appropriate choice for the underlined segment.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 1 (Back against the wall)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To give one a long rope&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;किसी को स्वतंत्रता देना&lt;/span&gt;): To allow someone the freedom to act as they please, even if it might lead to trouble.\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The manager decided &lt;strong&gt;to give the new employee a long rope&lt;/strong&gt; to see how he handled responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To go to the dogs&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;बिगड़ जाना&lt;/span&gt;): To deteriorate or decline in quality, value, or success.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The business &lt;strong&gt;went to the dogs&lt;/strong&gt; after the owner mismanaged it.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To give currency&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;लोकप्रिय बनाना&lt;/span&gt;): To make something widely known or accepted.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The media &lt;strong&gt;gave currency&lt;/strong&gt; to the rumour about the celebrity&amp;#39;s secret wedding.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
