          "&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Transparent&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Opaque&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means not allowing light to pass through; it is something that is not transparent or clear. (अपारदर्शी)\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The frosted glass on the window is &lt;strong&gt;opaque&lt;/strong&gt; and prevents anyone from seeing inside.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Transparent&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to something that allows light to pass through so that objects behind can be clearly seen. (पारदर्शी)\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;transparent &lt;/strong&gt;plastic sheet allowed us to see the contents inside the package.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the opposite of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Opaque&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Transparent&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Transparent&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;ul&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cloudy&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;धुंधला&lt;/span&gt;): Not clear or transparent; filled with clouds or resembling a cloud.\n\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The sky was &lt;strong&gt;cloudy &lt;/strong&gt;before the heavy rain started.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dull&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;मंद&lt;/span&gt;): Lacking brightness or vividness; not lively.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;dull &lt;/strong&gt;surface of the old mirror made it hard to see reflections.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dark&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अंधकारमय&lt;/span&gt;): Having little or no light; black or deep in colour.\n\t&lt;ul&gt;\n\t\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The room was &lt;strong&gt;dark &lt;/strong&gt;after the power outage.&lt;/li&gt;\n\t&lt;/ul&gt;\n\t&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n",
